## ğŸ¯ WHY THIS HAPPENS:

EmailJS templates need to know WHERE to send the email.

**Wrong (causes error):**
```
To Email: [empty]                    âŒ No recipient!
```

**Correct (works):**
```
To Email: {{to_email}}               âœ… Uses variable from License Manager
```

When you generate a license, the License Manager sends:
```javascript
{
  to_email: "customer@example.com",
  customer_name: "John Doe",
  license_key: "WOLF-A3D7-8K2M-5R9T-1D6F",
  // ... more data
}
```

EmailJS replaces `{{to_email}}` with the actual email address!

